"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905605","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-23","<p>This information is available in table 1.1 of the document “Prison population: 31 March 2018” at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/offender-management-statistics-quarterly-october-to-december-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/offender-management-statistics-quarterly-october-to-december-2017</a></p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-05-23T16:50:49.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905605/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905605/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-16","Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people in prison are not being held in relation to a criminal case.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","144872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905607","Home Office","false","2018-05-21","<p>In 2014-15 there were 29,315 matches between DNA profiles taken from crime scenes and subject records stored on the National DNA Database.</p><p>In 2015-16 there were 29,935 matches between DNA profiles taken from crime scenes and subject records stored on the National DNA Database.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-05-21T15:27:26.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905607/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905607/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-16","DNA: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many successful matches there were between DNA profiles taken from crime scenes and profiles stored on the national DNA database in (a) 2014-15 and (b) 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","144873"
