"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905612","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-21","<p>This Government is committed to introducing discounted travel options for young people. The 26-30 railcard is currently being tested through an industry-led trial. The Rail Delivery Group is overseeing this trial and the railcard’s implementation. This was announced as part of the Budget by the Chancellor in November 2017 and the Government continues to monitor the progress of this trial. We await further detail from the industry on how a national roll of the railcard can best be delivered.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-05-21T16:35:52.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905612/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905612/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-16","Railways: Concessions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether it remains the Government's policy to roll-out the 26-30 year railcard scheme throughout the UK.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","144971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905613","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-29","<p>The attached table shows the number of individuals released on HDC in England and Wales each month for the last two years for which data is available.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-29T13:42:33.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905613/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905613/answer","Copy of Copy of PQ 144875.xlsx","Copy of Copy of PQ 144875.xlsx","Table","Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905613/answer","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905613/answer/previousversion/60358","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-16","Prisoners' Release: Curfews","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been released from prison on Home Detention Curfew in each month in the last two years; and what offence each person released on curfew had committed.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","144875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905614","Home Office","false","2018-05-21","<p>The Home Office publishes police recorded crime and outcomes open data tables on a quarterly basis. The most recent publication covers recorded crime and outcomes data to the year ending December 2017.</p><p>Information on community resolutions for the last three years, broken down by offence type, can be found in the published open data tables released with the most recent police recorded crime and outcomes publication:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-recorded-crime-open-data-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-recorded-crime-open-data-tables</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-05-21T15:58:00.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905614/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905614/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-16","Alternatives to Prosecution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many community resolutions there have been by offence in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","144876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905615","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-23","<p>The Department does not hold this information centrally.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-05-23T10:39:36.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905615/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905615/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-16","Doctors: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many doctors currently working in the NHS have been convicted of (a) manslaughter, (b) clinical medical negligence and (c) culpable homicide.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","144877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905616","Department for Education","false","2018-05-21","<p>All schools must ensure that the teaching of Relationships and Sex Education (RSE) is inclusive to the needs of all pupils, whatever their developing sexuality or identity. Schools are required to comply with the Equality Act 2010 and any concerns that they are not doing so should be taken up with the school in the first instance.</p><p> </p><p>The Department recently conducted an engagement exercise with a wide range of expert stakeholders to support the introduction of compulsory RSE in secondary schools. This has included hosting an equalities roundtable and bilateral meetings with LGBT groups and faith organisations. The engagement process included an extensive call for evidence to seek views on what should be included in these subjects. Using the evidence gathered during this process, the Government will develop the regulations and accompanying statutory guidance for these subjects and both will be subject to public consultation followed by a debate on the regulations in Parliament.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","144973","2018-05-21T15:49:15.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905616/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905616/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-16","Sex and Relationship Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans his Department has to ensure that relationships and sex education is (a) impartial and (b) LGBT-inclusive in all types of schools.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","144972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905617","Department for Education","false","2018-05-21","<p>All schools must ensure that the teaching of Relationships and Sex Education (RSE) is inclusive to the needs of all pupils, whatever their developing sexuality or identity. Schools are required to comply with the Equality Act 2010 and any concerns that they are not doing so should be taken up with the school in the first instance.</p><p> </p><p>The Department recently conducted an engagement exercise with a wide range of expert stakeholders to support the introduction of compulsory RSE in secondary schools. This has included hosting an equalities roundtable and bilateral meetings with LGBT groups and faith organisations. The engagement process included an extensive call for evidence to seek views on what should be included in these subjects. Using the evidence gathered during this process, the Government will develop the regulations and accompanying statutory guidance for these subjects and both will be subject to public consultation followed by a debate on the regulations in Parliament.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","144972","2018-05-21T15:49:15.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905617/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905617/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-16","Sex and Relationship Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department plans to take to ensure that faith schools are compliant with the Equality Act 2010 when teaching relationships and sex education.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","144973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905618","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-23","<p>The Department did examine this as part of the wider Blue Badge reform programme but took the decision not to extend eligibility to people with temporary disabilities as this would have put at risk the sustainability of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has issued local authorities with advice on how they can use existing powers to provide locally determined parking concessions within their areas such as provision of badges to those with temporary conditions. The advice provided can be viewed at<strong>:</strong></p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/people-with-severe-temporary-impairments-advice-to-local-authorities" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/people-with-severe-temporary-impairments-advice-to-local-authorities</a></p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-05-23T10:16:05.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905618/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905618/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-16","Blue Badge Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Government has made an assessment of the potential merits of introducing a temporary Blue Badge scheme for people with temporary but debilitating and incapacitating injuries and conditions.","false","Biography information for Alex Chalk","Cheltenham","Alex Chalk","144952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905619","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-21","<p>The Government takes its defence exports responsibilities extremely seriously. We operate some of the most robust export controls in the world. We have no information to suggest that UK supplied equipment has been used in contravention of UK arms licensing criteria.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-21T16:51:53.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905619/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905619/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-16","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make an assessment of whether UK arms were used at the Gaza border against protesters.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","144790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905620","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-23","<p>No central assessment has been made of the contribution of undernutrition to the number of falls by older people.</p><p> </p><p>The Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) Regulations 2014 cover the fundamental standards below which care must not drop, including meeting the nutritional and hydration needs of users. The regulations, which are considered during Care Quality Commission inspections, specify that people who use services must have their nutritional needs assessed and mean that the risk of malnutrition and dehydration while they receive care and treatment is reduced.</p><p> </p><p>To help tackle malnutrition in acute and community settings, NHS England published guidance on ‘Commissioning excellent nutrition and hydration’ in October 2015. The implementation of this guidance is a matter for the local National Health Service. The guidance is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/nut-hyd/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/nut-hyd/</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-23T10:55:56.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905620/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/905620/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-16","Malnutrition: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the contribution of undernutrition to the number of falls by elderly people.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","144857"
